visual.name: LongTextViewer
visual.description: This visual helps you display long text from your data set in Power BI. When you bind the text to the visual, it wraps the text and scrolls vertically as needed. If your data set includes multiple rows of long text, they are shown one after the other. Updates: Number formatting is supported. Improved formatting and scrolling. Split text across lines.

fillColor.description: Font color for lines of text.

fontSize.description: Font size for lines of text (pt).

scrollable.description: Show scrollbars when the text is too long to fit.

verAlignment.description: Vertical alignment to apply to a line of text.

horAlignment.description: Horizontal alignment to apply to a line of text.

textTransform.description: Text transform to apply to a line of text.

fontFamily.description: Font family to apply to the line of text. Default is 'Arial'.

marginBefore.description: Margin before a line of text (em).

marginAfter.description: Margin after a line of text (em).

newLineChar.description: Provide a string with which to split text into separate lines. The provided string is removed from the text before it is displayed.
